{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EXyrpKgvm4pE5m6sEAhHgj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I can see the RBAC resources are there. Now let me create the manifest for the CockroachDB cluster deployment.\n\nI need to create:\n1. Headless Service: crdb-cluster (for internal DNS)\n2. Public Service: crdb-cluster-public (for external access)\n3. StatefulSet: crdb-cluster with 3 replicas\n4. PodDisruptionBudget to ensure quorum\n\nKey labels:\n- app.kubernetes.io/name: cockroachdb\n- app.kubernetes.io/instance: crdb-cluster\n\nFor the insecure CockroachDB cluster:\nEach pod gets a stable DNS name through the headless service, so crdb-cluster-0, crdb-cluster-1, and crdb-cluster-2 can discover each other via their fully qualified domain names. The startup command joins them together using those DNS addresses to form the cluster.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":358,"cache_read_input_tokens":28644,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":358},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0bef32aa-7ad1-447d-9ba2-09e05d9913af","uuid":"4b3ca63b-2023-418d-b37b-8cbf35ad1d04","request_id":"req_011Ccc2NbMXHzge9D4MMbdmZ"}
