{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MDheqgbgw2Yw8j8SAwKC2X","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The CockroachDB cluster is fully deployed and healthy. Here's a summary of what was deployed:\n\n**Resources created:**\n- `Service/crdb-cluster` — headless service (ClusterIP: None) for pod DNS, ports 26257/8080\n- `Service/crdb-cluster-public` — regular ClusterIP service for client access, ports 26257/8080\n- `StatefulSet/crdb-cluster` — 3 replicas, `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` (required so all nodes start simultaneously to form quorum), image `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0`, insecure mode\n- `PodDisruptionBudget/crdb-cluster-pdb` — `minAvailable: 2` ensures voluntary disruptions never drop below quorum\n- 3× `PersistentVolumeClaim` (10Gi each, all Bound)\n\n**Cluster state:**\n- All 3 nodes `is_available=true, is_live=true`\n- Each advertises via its full DNS name (`crdb-cluster-{0,1,2}.crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local`)\n\n**Note:** After deploying a fresh CockroachDB cluster, `cockroach init` must be run once to initialize the cluster — this is a one-time bootstrap step, not a sign of misconfiguration."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1401,"cache_read_input_tokens":37769,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1401},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0bef32aa-7ad1-447d-9ba2-09e05d9913af","uuid":"e55fbb6a-a82f-4b98-8eb5-557d6e16bd20","request_id":"req_011Ccc31P3dcsMm4oH58mVrk"}
